                    </span>
                   </li>
                   <li>
                    <span class="plainlinks">
                     <a class="external text" href="https://www.smogon.com/dex/dp/pokemon/linoone/" rel="nofollow">
                      Generation IV
                     </a>
                    </span>
                   </li>

                     </a>
                    </span>

                    <span class="plainlinks">

                  </a>

        </table>
        <p>
         <b>
          Linoone
         </b>
         (
         <a href="/wiki/List_of_Japanese_Pok%C3%A9mon_names" title="List of Japanese Pokémon names">
          Japanese
         </a>
         :
         <b>
          マッスグマ
         </b>
         <i>
          Massuguma
         </i>
         ) is a
         <a href="/wiki/Normal_(type)" title="Normal (type)">
          Normal-type
         </a>
         <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_(species)" title="Pokémon (species)">
          Pokémon
         </a>
         introduced in
         <a href="/wiki/Generation_III" title="Generation III">
          Generation III
         </a>
         .
        </p>
        <p>
         It
         <a href="/wiki/Evolution" title="Evolution">
          evolves
         </a>
         from
         <a href="/wiki/Zigzagoon_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Zigzagoon (Pokémon)">
          Zigzagoon
         </a>
         starting at
         <a href="/wiki/Level" title="Level">
          level
         </a>
         20.
        </p>
        <p>
         In
         <a href="/wiki/Galar" title="Galar">
          Galar
         </a>
         , Linoone has a dual-type
         <a href="/wiki/Dark_(type)" title="Dark (type)">
          Dark
         </a>
         /
         <a href="/wiki/Normal_(type)" title="Normal (type)">
          Normal
         </a>
         <a href="/wiki/Regional_form" title="Regional form">
          regional form
         </a>
         . It evolves from Galarian Zigzagoon starting at level 20 and evolves into
         <a href="/wiki/Obstagoon_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Obstagoon (Pokémon)">
          Obstagoon
         </a>
         when leveled up starting at level 35 during the
         <a href="/wiki/Time-based_Evolution" title="Time-based Evolution">
          night
         </a>
         . Hoennian Linoone is not known to evolve into any other Pokémon.
        </p>

        <h2>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="Biology">
          Biology
         </span>
        </h2>
        <p>
         Linoone is a slender-bodied, quadrupedal
         <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_(species)" title="Pokémon (species)">
          Pokémon
         </a>
         . Most of its fur is colored tan, but it has several brown stripes. One long stripe stretches the length of its body before ending in an arrowhead shape on its forehead. There are additional stripes on each side of its bushy tail and on its cheeks. It has sharp, elongated claws and small pointed teeth. It has small, tuft-like ears, long cheek fur, and blue eyes.
        </p>
        <p>
         Linoone can run up to
         <span class="explain" title="100 kilometers per hour">
          60 miles per hour
         </span>
         , but it can only run in a straight line, and has to stop before it can make a turn. Because of this behavior, it often fails to catch prey, and struggles on roads that are curving or winding. When it sees prey underwater in ponds, it leaps in and uses its razor-sharp claws to catch and take it down. Linoone's fur is strong and supple, and the shed hairs are used to make high-quality shaving brushes. As shown in the
         <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_the_Series:_Ruby_and_Sapphire" title="Pokémon the Series: Ruby and Sapphire">
          <i>
           Pokémon the Series: Ruby and Sapphire
          </i>
         </a>
         episode
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/AG112" title="AG112">
           Showdown at Linoone
          </a>
         </i>
         , Linoone has an attraction to anything round and will grab any orb-shaped object it sees if given the chance. It often carries a snatched object in its expandable cheek pouches and deposits it in any of a number of secret stashes it keeps on its territory. Linoone tends to live in
         <a href="/wiki/List_of_Pok%C3%A9mon_by_habitat#Grassland_Pokémon" title="List of Pokémon by habitat">
          grasslands
         </a>
         .
        </p>
        <h3>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="Forms">
          Forms
         </span>
        </h3>
        <p>
         Linoone has a
         <a href="/wiki/Regional_form" title="Regional form">
          regional form
         </a>
         : Galarian Linoone.
        </p>
        <p>
         Galarian Linoone has a black-and-white color scheme, with longer fur on its ears. Around its red eyes are patterned stripes shaped like a shooting star. It has longer claws with gray fur surrounding the front feet, and it has a long red tongue that sticks out of its mouth.
        </p>
        <p>
         Galarian Linoone are known to be rash and fearless, preferring to recklessly challenge opponents that are stronger than itself. Linoone is known to use its long tongue to taunt opponents. Once the foe is fully enraged, Linoone will hurl itself at them, tackling them by force. These traits make Galarian Linoone very popular among unhappy and angry youths in
         <a href="/wiki/Galar" title="Galar">
          Galar
         </a>
         , who have nowhere to take out their anger and frustrations. By charging at up to 60 miles per hour, it can deliver powerful
         <a href="/wiki/Tackle_(move)" title="Tackle (move)">
          Tackles
         </a>
         and
         <a href="/wiki/Headbutt_(move)" title="Headbutt (move)">
          Headbutts
         </a>
         with enough destructive force to even knock away a car. Linoone can be thrown off balance should it miss, however.
         <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-1">
          <a href="#cite_note-1">
           [1]
          </a>
         </sup>
         The harsh environments in the Galar region, along with the fierce competition among the species, allows Linoone's survival instincts to improve, leading to the ability to evolve into
         <a href="/wiki/Obstagoon_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Obstagoon (Pokémon)">
          Obstagoon
         </a>
         .
         <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-2">
          <a href="#cite_note-2">
           [2]
          </a>
         </sup>
        </p>
        <h3>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="Evolution">
          Evolution
         </span>
        </h3>
        <p>
         Linoone evolves from
         <a href="/wiki/Zigzagoon_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Zigzagoon (Pokémon)">
          Zigzagoon
         </a>
        </p>
        <p>
         <a href="/wiki/Galarian_form" title="Galarian form">
          Galarian
         </a>
         Linoone evolves from Galarian Zigzagoon and evolves into
         <a href="/wiki/Obstagoon_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Obstagoon (Pokémon)">
          Obstagoon
         </a>
         .
        </p>
        <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: space-evenly">
         <div style="max-width:100%; text-align:center;">

        <h2>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="Game_data">
          Game data
         </span>
        </h2>
        <h3>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="NPC_appearances">
          NPC appearances
         </span>
        </h3>
        <p>
         <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Pinball:_Ruby_%26_Sapphire" title="Pokémon Pinball: Ruby &amp; Sapphire">
          Pokémon Pinball: Ruby &amp; Sapphire
         </a>
         : When
         <a href="/wiki/Chikorita_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Chikorita (Pokémon)">
          Chikorita
         </a>
         uses
         <a href="/wiki/Razor_Leaf_(move)" title="Razor Leaf (move)">
          Razor Leaf
         </a>
         on the Ruby Field, two Linoone will pop out. Hitting the left Linoone will make a
         <a href="/wiki/Gulpin_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Gulpin (Pokémon)">
          Gulpin
         </a>
         appear, activating Travel Mode when there are three Gulpin on the table. Hitting the right Linoone will change the stance of
         <a href="/wiki/Makuhita_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Makuhita (Pokémon)">
          Makuhita
         </a>
         allowing it to punch the ball towards the Upgrade.
        </p>

                     </span>

                    <span class="sc">
                     Linoone
                    </span>
                    always runs full speed and only in straight lines. If facing an obstacle, it makes a right-angle turn to evade it. This
                    <span class="sc">
                     Pok
                    </span>
                    é
                    <span class="sc">
                     mon
                    </span>
                    is very challenged by gently curving roads.
                   </td>

                    <span class="sc">
                     Linoone
                    </span>
                    will make a beeline straight for the prey at a full run. While this
                    <span class="sc">
                     Pok
                    </span>
                    é
                    <span class="sc">
                     mon
                    </span>
                    is capable of topping
                    <span class="explain" title="100 km/h">
                     60 mph
                    </span>
                    , it has to come to a screeching halt before it can turn.

                     </span>
                    </a>
                   </th>
                   <td class="roundy" style="vertical-align: middle; border: 1px solid #9DC1B7; padding-left:3px;">
                    It is exceedingly fast if it only has to run in a straight line. When it spots pond-dwelling prey underwater, it quickly leaps in and catches it with its sharp claws.
                   </td>

        <h3>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="Learnset">
          Learnset
         </span>
        </h3>
        <p>
         Linoone is available in
         <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Sword_and_Shield" title="Pokémon Sword and Shield">
          Sword and Shield
         </a>
         and
         <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Brilliant_Diamond_and_Shining_Pearl" title="Pokémon Brilliant Diamond and Shining Pearl">
          Brilliant Diamond and Shining Pearl
         </a>
         .
        </p>
        <h4>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="By_leveling_up">
          By
          <a href="/wiki/Level" title="Level">
           leveling up
          </a>
         </span>
        </h4>
        <h5>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="Linoone_3">
          Linoone
         </span>
        </h5>
        <table class="roundy" style="margin:auto; background: #9FA19F; border: 3px solid #676967;">
         <tbody>
          <tr>
           <td class="roundytop" style="background: #C1C2C1;">
            <table style="background:transparent;" width="100%">
             <tbody>
              <tr>

            <ul>
             <li>
              <b>
               Bold
              </b>
              indicates a move that gets
              <a href="/wiki/Same-type_attack_bonus" title="Same-type attack bonus">
               <span style="color:#000;">
                STAB
               </span>
              </a>
              when used by Linoone
             </li>
             <li>
              <i>
               Italic
              </i>
              indicates a move that gets STAB only when used by an Evolution of Linoone
             </li>
             <li>
              Click on the generation numbers at the top to see TM moves from other generations
             </li>
            </ul>

              </b>

              <a href="/wiki/Same-type_attack_bonus" title="Same-type attack bonus">

               </span>
              </a>

              </i>
              indicates a move that gets STAB only when used by an Evolution of Linoone

          <tr>
           <td class="roundybottom" style="background:#C1C2C1; font-size: 90%; line-height:10px;">
            <ul>
             <li>
              Moves marked with an asterisk (*) must be
              <a href="/wiki/Chain_breeding" title="Chain breeding">
               <span style="color:#000;">
                chain bred
               </span>
              </a>
              onto Linoone in Generation VIII
             </li>
             <li>
              Moves marked with a double dagger (‡) can only be bred from a Pokémon who learned the move in an earlier generation.
             </li>
             <li>
              Moves marked with a superscript game abbreviation can only be bred onto Linoone in that game.
             </li>
             <li>
              <b>
               Bold
              </b>
              indicates a move that gets
              <a href="/wiki/Same-type_attack_bonus" title="Same-type attack bonus">
               <span style="color:#000;">
                STAB
               </span>
              </a>
              when used by Linoone
             </li>
             <li>
              <i>
               Italic
              </i>
              indicates a move that gets STAB only when used by an Evolution of Linoone
             </li>
             <li>
              Click on the generation numbers at the top to see Egg moves from other generations
             </li>
            </ul>
           </td>

          <tr>
           <td class="roundybottom" style="background:#C1C2C1; font-size: 90%; line-height:10px;">
            <ul>
             <li>
              Moves marked with an asterisk (*) must be
              <a href="/wiki/Chain_breeding" title="Chain breeding">
               <span style="color:#000;">
                chain bred
               </span>
              </a>
              onto Linoone in Generation VIII
             </li>
             <li>
              Moves marked with a double dagger (‡) can only be bred from a Pokémon who learned the move in an earlier generation.
             </li>
             <li>
              Moves marked with a superscript game abbreviation can only be bred onto Linoone in that game.
             </li>
             <li>
              <b>
               Bold
              </b>
              indicates a move that gets
              <a href="/wiki/Same-type_attack_bonus" title="Same-type attack bonus">
               <span style="color:#000;">
                STAB
               </span>
              </a>
              when used by Linoone
             </li>
             <li>
              <i>
               Italic
              </i>
              indicates a move that gets STAB only when used by an Evolution of Linoone
             </li>
             <li>
              Click on the generation numbers at the top to see Egg moves from other generations
             </li>
            </ul>
           </td>
          </tr>

               </span>

             </li>

          <tr>
           <td class="roundybottom" colspan="11" style="background:#C1C2C1; font-size: 90%; line-height:10px;">
            <ul>
             <li>
              Transferred Pokémon only retain these moves in
              <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Sword_and_Shield" title="Pokémon Sword and Shield">
               <span style="color:#000;">
                Pokémon Sword and Shield
               </span>
              </a>
             </li>
             <li>
              A striped background indicates a generation in which the move can only be obtained via event or as a special move
             </li>
             <li>
              <b>
               Bold
              </b>
              indicates a move that gets
              <a href="/wiki/Same-type_attack_bonus" title="Same-type attack bonus">
               <span style="color:#000;">
                STAB
               </span>
              </a>
              when used by Linoone
             </li>
             <li>
              <i>
               Italic
              </i>
              indicates a move that gets STAB only when used by an Evolution of Linoone
             </li>
             <li>
              <b>
               <span style="color:#f00;">
                ×
               </span>
              </b>
              indicates a move that
              <a href="/wiki/List_of_moves_by_availability_in_Generation_VIII" title="List of moves by availability in Generation VIII">
               <span style="color:#000;">
                cannot be used in Sword and Shield
               </span>
              </a>
             </li>
             <li>
              Click on the generation numbers at the top to see transfer-only moves for other generations
             </li>
            </ul>
           </td>
          </tr>
         </tbody>
        </table>
        <h3>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="Side_game_data">
          Side game data
         </span>
        </h3>
        <h4>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="Linoone_8">
          Linoone
         </span>
        </h4>
        <table style="margin:auto; background: #9FA19F; border-radius: 10px; -moz-border-radius: 10px; -webkit-border-radius: 10px; -khtml-border-radius: 10px; -icab-border-radius: 10px; -o-border-radius: 10px; border: 3px solid #676967;" width="650px">
         <tbody>

                      <img alt="Spr 8s 264G.png" data-file-height="1024" data-file-width="1024" decoding="async" height="400" loading="lazy" src="https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/c/c6/Spr_8s_264G.png/400px-Spr_8s_264G.png" srcset="https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/c/c6/Spr_8s_264G.png/600px-Spr_8s_264G.png 1.5x, https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/c/c6/Spr_8s_264G.png/800px-Spr_8s_264G.png 2x" width="400"/>
                     </a>
                    </div>
                   </th>
                   <th class="roundybr" style="border-right:1px solid #000; border-bottom:1px solid #000;">
                    <div style="height:157px; width:157px; display:inline-flex; justify-content:center; align-items:center; overflow: hidden;">

                     </a>

                   </th>
                  </tr>
                 </tbody>
                </table>
               </td>

           </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
           <th class="roundy" style="background:#FFF; border: 3px solid #EBC081; padding:3px;">
            This Pokémon is unavailable in Generation IX.
           </th>
          </tr>

        <h2>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="In_animation">
          In animation
         </span>
        </h2>
        <h3>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="Main_series">
          Main series
         </span>
        </h3>
        <div class="thumb tright">
         <div class="thumbinner" style="width:252px;">
          <a class="image" href="/wiki/File:Solana_Linoone.png">
           <img alt="" class="thumbimage" data-file-height="480" data-file-width="640" decoding="async" height="188" loading="lazy" src="https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/c/c3/Solana_Linoone.png/250px-Solana_Linoone.png" srcset="https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/c/c3/Solana_Linoone.png/375px-Solana_Linoone.png 1.5x, https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/c/c3/Solana_Linoone.png/500px-Solana_Linoone.png 2x" width="250"/>
          </a>
          <div class="thumbcaption">
           <div class="magnify">
            <a class="internal" href="/wiki/File:Solana_Linoone.png" title="Enlarge">
            </a>
           </div>
           Linoone in
           <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_the_Series:_Ruby_and_Sapphire" title="Pokémon the Series: Ruby and Sapphire">
            <i>
             Pokémon the Series: Ruby and Sapphire
            </i>
           </a>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
        <h4>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="Major_appearances">
          Major appearances
         </span>
        </h4>
        <p>
         Linoone made its main series debut in
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/AG112" title="AG112">
           Showdown at Linoone
          </a>
         </i>
         , under the ownership of
         <a href="/wiki/Kimmy_Shoney" title="Kimmy Shoney">
          Kimmy Shoney
         </a>
         and the
         <a href="/wiki/Nickname" title="Nickname">
          nickname
         </a>
         of Tokin. It had developed a bad habit of stealing anything in sight.
        </p>
        <p>
         In
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/AG155" title="AG155">
           The Green Guardian
          </a>
         </i>
         ,
         <a href="/wiki/Solana" title="Solana">
          Solana
         </a>
         used her
         <a href="/wiki/Capture_Styler" title="Capture Styler">
          Capture Styler
         </a>
         on three Linoone so they could slash vines created by a
         <a href="/wiki/Celebi_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Celebi (Pokémon)">
          Celebi
         </a>
         .
        </p>
        <p>
         In the original timeline in
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/M12" title="M12">
           Arceus and the Jewel of Life
          </a>
         </i>
         , a
         <a href="/wiki/Hypnosis_(move)" title="Hypnosis (move)">
          hypnotized
         </a>
         <a href="/wiki/Damos" title="Damos">
          Damos
         </a>
         commanded his five Linoone to attack
         <a href="/wiki/Arceus_(M12)" title="Arceus (M12)">
          Arceus
         </a>
         with
         <a href="/wiki/Shock_Wave_(move)" title="Shock Wave (move)">
          Shock Wave
         </a>
         . When Ash and
         <a href="/wiki/Ash%27s_friends" title="Ash's friends">
          his friends
         </a>
         traveled to the past to prevent this,
         <a href="/wiki/Marcus" title="Marcus">
          Marcus
         </a>
         , the one responsible for hypnotizing Damos, managed to use the Linoone again to attack Arceus.
        </p>
        <p>
         In
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/XY046" title="XY046">
           The Clumsy Crier Quiets the Chaos!
          </a>
         </i>
         , a
         <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Breeder_(Trainer_class)" title="Pokémon Breeder (Trainer class)">
          Pokémon Breeder
         </a>
         's Linoone was playing with a
         <a href="/wiki/Bidoof_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Bidoof (Pokémon)">
          Bidoof
         </a>
         and a
         <a href="/wiki/Teddiursa_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Teddiursa (Pokémon)">
          Teddiursa
         </a>
         when they were all attacked by a rampaging
         <a href="/wiki/Salamence_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Salamence (Pokémon)">
          Salamence
         </a>
         . Linoone was then taken to a
         <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Center" title="Pokémon Center">
          Pokémon Center
         </a>
         and healed with the help of
         <a href="/wiki/Nurse_Joy" title="Nurse Joy">
          Nurse Joy
         </a>
         and her
         <a href="/wiki/Nurse_Joy%27s_Wigglytuff" title="Nurse Joy's Wigglytuff">
          Wigglytuff
         </a>
         .
        </p>
        <h4>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="Minor_appearances">
          Minor appearances
         </span>
        </h4>
        <p>
         Multiple Linoone debuted in
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/M06" title="M06">
           Jirachi: Wish Maker
          </a>
         </i>
         , as residents of
         <a href="/wiki/Forina" title="Forina">
          Forina
         </a>
         .
        </p>
        <p>
         In
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/DP005" title="DP005">
           Gettin' Twiggy With It!
          </a>
         </i>
         , a Linoone was nursed back to health by
         <a href="/wiki/Clara" title="Clara">
          Clara
         </a>
         .
        </p>
        <p>
         A Linoone appeared in
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/DP088" title="DP088">
           Camping It Up!
          </a>
         </i>
         .
        </p>
        <p>
         In
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/M13" title="M13">
           Zoroark: Master of Illusions
          </a>
         </i>
         , a Linoone was living in
         <a href="/wiki/Crown_City" title="Crown City">
          Crown City
         </a>
         . It worked with several other Pokémon in surrounding
         <a href="/wiki/Zorua_(M13)" title="Zorua (M13)">
          Zorua
         </a>
         in the park in order to attack him as retribution for what
         <a href="/wiki/Zoroark_(M13)" title="Zoroark (M13)">
          Zoroark
         </a>
         did to the city. Before a fight broke out, the Zigzagoon, along with the other Pokémon, were calmed down by
         <a href="/wiki/Celebi_(M13)" title="Celebi (M13)">
          Celebi
         </a>
         .
        </p>
        <p>
         A Linoone appeared in
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/XY002" title="XY002">
           Lumiose City Pursuit!
          </a>
         </i>
         ,
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/XY041" title="XY041">
           Foggy Pokémon Orienteering!
          </a>
         </i>
         , and
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/XY137" title="XY137">
           Battling With a Clean Slate!
          </a>
         </i>
         ; and in flashbacks in
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/XYS01" title="XYS01">
           Mega Evolution Special I
          </a>
         </i>
         and
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/XY068" title="XY068">
           Garchomp's Mega Bond!
          </a>
         </i>
         at
         <a href="/wiki/Professor_Sycamore_(anime)" title="Professor Sycamore (anime)">
          Professor Sycamore
         </a>
         's lab.
        </p>
        <p>
         In
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/M17" title="M17">
           Diancie and the Cocoon of Destruction
          </a>
         </i>
         , multiple Linoone were living in
         <a href="/wiki/Allearth_Forest" title="Allearth Forest">
          Allearth Forest
         </a>
         .
        </p>
        <p>
         In
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/JN007" title="JN007">
           Serving Up the Flute Cup!
          </a>
         </i>
         , a
         <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Trainer" title="Pokémon Trainer">
          Trainer
         </a>
         's Linoone competed in the
         <a href="/wiki/Battle_Frontier_Flute_Cup" title="Battle Frontier Flute Cup">
          Battle Frontier Flute Cup
         </a>
         , only to be defeated by
         <a href="/wiki/Ash%27s_Pikachu" title="Ash's Pikachu">
          Pikachu
         </a>
         .
        </p>

                </a>

                <span class="explain" title="100 kilometers per hour">

                </span>

         A
         <a href="/wiki/Wild_Pok%C3%A9mon" title="Wild Pokémon">
          wild
         </a>

         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/PG09" title="PG09">

          </a>
         </i>
         .
         <br clear="all"/>
        </p>

        <div class="thumb tright">

        <h3>
         <span id="Ash_.26_Pikachu">
         </span>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="Ash_&amp;_Pikachu">
          Ash &amp; Pikachu
         </span>
        </h3>
        <p>
         Linoone appeared in
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/SP35" title="SP35">
           A 'Thank You' That Transcends Time
          </a>
         </i>
         .
        </p>
        <h3>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="Movie_adaptations">
          Movie adaptations
         </span>
        </h3>
        <p>
         A Linoone appeared in the
         <a href="/wiki/Diancie_and_the_Cocoon_of_Destruction_(manga)" title="Diancie and the Cocoon of Destruction (manga)">
          manga adaptation
         </a>
         of
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/M17" title="M17">
           Diancie and the Cocoon of Destruction
          </a>
         </i>
         as a resident of
         <a href="/wiki/Allearth_Forest" title="Allearth Forest">
          Allearth Forest
         </a>
         .
        </p>
        <h3>
         <span id="Pok.C3.A9mon_Adventures">
         </span>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="Pokémon_Adventures">
          Pokémon Adventures
         </span>
        </h3>
        <p>
         In
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/PS306" title="PS306">
           Pinsir Me, I Must Be Dreaming
          </a>
         </i>
         ,
         <a href="/wiki/Emerald_(Adventures)" title="Emerald (Adventures)">
          Emerald
         </a>
         used a Linoone holding a
         <a href="/wiki/Choice_Band" title="Choice Band">
          Choice Band
         </a>
         to breeze through the
         <a href="/wiki/Battle_Factory_(Generation_III)" title="Battle Factory (Generation III)">
          Battle Factory
         </a>
         . Because he was a rental Pokémon he had just received, his extra-powerful
         <a href="/wiki/Frustration_(move)" title="Frustration (move)">
          Frustration
         </a>
         went a long way before he challenged
         <a href="/wiki/Noland" title="Noland">
          Noland
         </a>
         .
        </p>
        <p>
         The Battle Factory rented a Linoone, which was stolen by
         <a href="/wiki/Guile_Hideout" title="Guile Hideout">
          Guile Hideout
         </a>
         in
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/PS315" title="PS315">
           Skirting Around Surskit I
          </a>
         </i>
         .
        </p>
        <p>
         A
         <a href="/wiki/Galarian_form" title="Galarian form">
          Galarian
         </a>
         Linoone debuted under the ownership of a
         <a href="/wiki/Team_Yell_Grunt_(Trainer_class)" title="Team Yell Grunt (Trainer class)">
          Team Yell Grunt
         </a>
         in
         <i>
          <a href="/wiki/PASS04" title="PASS04">
           Zap!! A Rising Beam of Light
          </a>
         </i>
         .
         <br clear="all"/>
        </p>
        <h2>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="In_the_TCG">
          In the TCG
         </span>
        </h2>
        <dl>
         <dd>
          <i>
           Main article:
           <a href="/wiki/Linoone_(TCG)" title="Linoone (TCG)">
            Linoone (TCG)
           </a>
          </i>
         </dd>
        </dl>
        <h2>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="In_the_TFG">
          In the TFG
         </span>
        </h2>
        <p>
         One Linoone figure has been released.
        </p>
        <ul>
         <li>
          <a href="/wiki/Groundbreakers_(TFG)" title="Groundbreakers (TFG)">
           Groundbreakers
          </a>
          :
          <a href="/wiki/Linoone_(Groundbreakers_19)" title="Linoone (Groundbreakers 19)">
           Linoone
          </a>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <h2>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="Trivia">
          Trivia
         </span>
        </h2>
        <ul>
         <li>
          Linoone is the only
          <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_(species)" title="Pokémon (species)">
           Pokémon
          </a>
          that can use the
          <a href="/wiki/Lookalike_Item#Mix_Elixir" title="Lookalike Item">
           Mix Elixir
          </a>
          in
          <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_Mystery_Dungeon:_Explorers_of_Sky" title="Pokémon Mystery Dungeon: Explorers of Sky">
           Pokémon Mystery Dungeon: Explorers of Sky
          </a>
          .
         </li>
         <li>
          Linoone has the same
          <a class="mw-disambig" href="/wiki/List_of_Pok%C3%A9mon_by_Hoenn_Pok%C3%A9dex_number" title="List of Pokémon by Hoenn Pokédex number">
           Hoenn Pokédex
          </a>
          and
          <a href="/wiki/List_of_Pok%C3%A9mon_by_Kalos_Pok%C3%A9dex_number" title="List of Pokémon by Kalos Pokédex number">
           Central Kalos Pokédex
          </a>
          numbers.
         </li>
         <li>
          Galarian Linoone and its
          <a href="/wiki/Shiny_Pok%C3%A9mon" title="Shiny Pokémon">
           Shiny
          </a>
          form were designed by
          <a href="/wiki/James_Turner" title="James Turner">
           James Turner
          </a>
          .
          <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3">
           <a href="#cite_note-3">
            [3]
           </a>
          </sup>
          <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4">
           <a href="#cite_note-4">
            [4]
           </a>
          </sup>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <h3>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="Origin">
          Origin
         </span>
        </h3>
        <p>
         Linoone's appearance is possibly a cross between the
         <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_badger" title="wp:European badger">
          European
         </a>
         or
         <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese_badger" title="wp:Japanese badger">
          Japanese badger
         </a>
         and a member of the
         <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/weasel" title="wp:weasel">
          weasel
         </a>
         and/or
         <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ferret" title="wp:ferret">
          ferret
         </a>
         family, or it may possibly be based on the
         <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ferret-badger" title="wp:ferret-badger">
          ferret-badger
         </a>
         or
         <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/striped_polecat" title="wp:striped polecat">
          striped polecat
         </a>
         . It also shares the same color scheme of
         <i>
          <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/raccoon_dog" title="wp:raccoon dog">
           tanuki
          </a>
         </i>
         . The word
         <i>
          tanuki
         </i>
         is used for both badgers and raccoon dogs in Japan, depending on the region. This may be the inspiration behind its mixture of traits, having similarities to both species. Its stripes slightly resemble flames and lightning, which may be a reference to
         <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Auto_Racing" title="wp:Auto Racing">
          race cars
         </a>
         , who typically use these patterns on their vehicles for show. Linoone may also be based on the legendary
         <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kamaitachi" title="wp:Kamaitachi">
          Kamaitachi
         </a>
         , which is usually depicted as lightning-fast weasels who wield razor-sharp claws which tear into their victims. There is a arrow symbol on its head which alludes to its tendecy to run in a straight line. Linoone's obsession with round objects may be inspired by the
         <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ramidreju" title="wp:Ramidreju">
          Ramidreju
         </a>
         , a long, weasel-like creature who has a desire for gold; or by the
         <i>
          tanuki'
         </i>
         s association with gold.
        </p>
        <p>
         Galarian Linoone appears to be more explicitly based on European badgers. Taking its evolved form
         <a href="/wiki/Obstagoon_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Obstagoon (Pokémon)">
          Obstagoon
         </a>
         under consideration, Galarian Linoone's color scheme, pointed tongue, and star marking around its eyes may also be inspired by
         <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glam_rock" title="wp:Glam rock">
          Glam rock
         </a>
         bands.
        </p>
        <p>
         Linoone's evolutionary line shares a common theme of movement where
         <a href="/wiki/Zigzagoon_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Zigzagoon (Pokémon)">
          Zigzagoon
         </a>
         moves in a zigzag pattern, Linoone moves in a straight line, and
         <a href="/wiki/Obstagoon_(Pok%C3%A9mon)" title="Obstagoon (Pokémon)">
          Obstagoon
         </a>
         blocks the way by obstructing it.
        </p>
        <h4>
         <span class="mw-headline" id="Name_origin">
          Name origin
         </span>
        </h4>
        <p>
         Linoone may be a combination of
         <i>
          line
         </i>
         (referring to its fur pattern and unusual habits) and
         <i>
          <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/raccoon" title="wp:raccoon">
           raccoon
          </a>
         </i>
         .
        </p>
        <p>
         Massuguma may be a combination of まっすぐ
         <i>
          massugu
         </i>
         (straight, as in a line) and アライグマ
         <i>
          araiguma
         </i>
         (
         <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/raccoon" title="wp:raccoon">
          raccoon
         </a>
         ) or 穴熊
         <i>
          anaguma
         </i>
         (
         <a class="extiw" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/badger" title="wp:badger">
          badger
         </a>
         ).
         <i>
          Guma
         </i>
         (from 熊
         <i>
          kuma
         </i>
         , "bear") as a suffix is often used for mammals that resemble bears.
        </p>

                </a>
                <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_in_Russia" title="Pokémon in Russia">
                 Russian
                </a>
               </td>
               <td>
                Лайнун
                <i>
                 Laynun
                </i>
               </td>
               <td>
                Transcription of English name
               </td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="background:#FFF">
               <td>
                <a class="image" href="/wiki/File:Thailand_Flag.png">
                 <img alt="Thailand Flag.png" class="thumbborder" data-file-height="213" data-file-width="320" decoding="async" height="13" loading="lazy" src="https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/e/e6/Thailand_Flag.png/20px-Thailand_Flag.png" srcset="https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/e/e6/Thailand_Flag.png/30px-Thailand_Flag.png 1.5x, https://archives.bulbagarden.net/media/upload/thumb/e/e6/Thailand_Flag.png/40px-Thailand_Flag.png 2x" width="20"/>
                </a>
                <a href="/wiki/Pok%C3%A9mon_in_Thailand" title="Pokémon in Thailand">
                 Thai
                </a>
               </td>
               <td>

       <script>
        // Initialize elements
appendElementIf({id: "adthrive-left-s", wAbove: 1520, wBelow: 1699, hAbove: 700});
appendElementIf({id: "adthrive-left-m", wAbove: 1700, wBelow: 1890, hAbove: 700});
appendElementIf({id: "adthrive-left-l", wAbove: 1891, hAbove: 700});

appendElementIf({id: "adthrive-right-s", wAbove: 945, wBelow: 1099, hAbove: 964});
appendElementIf({id: "adthrive-right-m", wAbove: 1100, wBelow: 1399, hAbove: 964});
appendElementIf({id: "adthrive-right-l", wAbove: 1400, hAbove: 964});
appendElementIf({id: "adthrive-right-rect", hBelow: 964});


// Appends element if condition is met
function appendElementIf({id, wAbove, wBelow, hAbove, hBelow}) {

	// find browser height
	var w = window.innerWidth;
	var h = window.innerHeight;

	// If true after browser size check then unit is added
	var condition = true;

	// Check size conditions
	if (wBelow && (w > wBelow)) condition = false;
	if (wAbove && (w < wAbove)) condition = false;

	if (hBelow && (h > hBelow)) condition = false;
	if (hAbove && (h < hAbove)) condition = false;

	// Append element if condition is met
	if (condition) {
		createAndAppendElement(id);
	}
}


// creates and appends a div element to the body
function createAndAppendElement(id)
{
	var atEl = document.createElement('div');
	atEl.id = id;
	document.body.appendChild(atEl);
}
       </script>

      <h3 id="p-search-label">
       <label for="searchInput">
